{
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Hi, my name is Tony",
            "start": 0.2,
            "duration": 1.204
        },
        {
            "text": "and this is \"Every Frame a Painting\",",
            "start": 1.405,
            "duration": 1.612
        },
        {
            "text": "where I analyze film form.",
            "start": 3.018,
            "duration": 1.753
        },
        {
            "text": "There's actually a lot of\ngreat videos on the internet",
            "start": 5.001,
            "duration": 2.041
        },
        {
            "text": "analyzing movie content or themes,",
            "start": 7.043,
            "duration": 1.958
        },
        {
            "text": "but I think we're missing stuff\nabout the actual form -",
            "start": 9.002,
            "duration": 2.34
        },
        {
            "text": "you know, the pictures and the sound.",
            "start": 11.343,
            "duration": 1.728
        },
        {
            "text": "Anyways, the movie\nI want to talk about today",
            "start": 17.9,
            "duration": 1.606
        },
        {
            "text": "is a fantastic example\nof craft and art.",
            "start": 19.507,
            "duration": 2.305
        },
        {
            "text": "This is Bong Joon-ho's film\n\"Mother\", from 2009.",
            "start": 21.901,
            "duration": 3.0
        },
        {
            "text": "If you haven't seen it,",
            "start": 24.902,
            "duration": 0.998
        },
        {
            "text": "it's kind of a wrong man murder mystery,",
            "start": 25.901,
            "duration": 2.001
        },
        {
            "text": "and if you don't know Bong Joon-ho,",
            "start": 27.903,
            "duration": 1.3
        },
        {
            "text": "he's awesome.",
            "start": 29.204,
            "duration": 1.2
        },
        {
            "text": "Dude is seriously the best.",
            "start": 30.405,
            "duration": 1.5
        },
        {
            "text": "Be forewarned, there are\nmajor spoilers for the whole film.",
            "start": 31.906,
            "duration": 2.999
        },
        {
            "text": "If you don't want to be spoiled,\nstop watching this and go watch the movie.",
            "start": 34.906,
            "duration": 3.0
        },
        {
            "text": "Ready? Okay.",
            "start": 37.907,
            "duration": 1.4
        },
        {
            "text": "So there's two techniques, combined,\nthat I want to bring up today.",
            "start": 45.0,
            "duration": 2.538
        },
        {
            "text": "The first is shooting important\nstory moments in profile.",
            "start": 47.539,
            "duration": 3.433
        },
        {
            "text": "The second is doing that\nwith a telephoto lens.",
            "start": 51.373,
            "duration": 2.329
        },
        {
            "text": "So normally, you shoot an actor,\nyou want to see their face.",
            "start": 54.303,
            "duration": 2.79
        },
        {
            "text": "If you bring the camera around to the front,",
            "start": 57.094,
            "duration": 1.624
        },
        {
            "text": "it's generally a better way for us to\nempathize or to see their emotions.",
            "start": 58.719,
            "duration": 2.968
        },
        {
            "text": "If you play something off\nthe profile of someone's face,",
            "start": 61.688,
            "duration": 2.242
        },
        {
            "text": "it's a little bit stranger.",
            "start": 63.931,
            "duration": 1.516
        },
        {
            "text": "It has a starkness to it.",
            "start": 65.449,
            "duration": 1.498
        },
        {
            "text": "Like this.",
            "start": 66.948,
            "duration": 0.9
        },
        {
            "text": "Versus this.",
            "start": 69.856,
            "duration": 1.188
        },
        {
            "text": "God. Stop. Oh god!",
            "start": 72.7,
            "duration": 2.199
        },
        {
            "text": "Now here's the weird part.",
            "start": 76.0,
            "duration": 1.164
        },
        {
            "text": "You throw on a telephoto lens,",
            "start": 77.165,
            "duration": 1.633
        },
        {
            "text": "and that compresses space.",
            "start": 78.799,
            "duration": 1.269
        },
        {
            "text": "We do it all the time\nin movies for close-ups.",
            "start": 80.069,
            "duration": 1.99
        },
        {
            "text": "It's more flattering",
            "start": 82.06,
            "duration": 1.055
        },
        {
            "text": "and it blows out the background,\nit gives this nice little bokeh.",
            "start": 83.116,
            "duration": 3.001
        },
        {
            "text": "But when you do it in profile,",
            "start": 86.15,
            "duration": 1.095
        },
        {
            "text": "it's not really a beauty shot.",
            "start": 87.246,
            "duration": 1.565
        },
        {
            "text": "It hides something.",
            "start": 88.812,
            "duration": 1.1
        },
        {
            "text": "Add a little camera operator shake,",
            "start": 89.913,
            "duration": 1.587
        },
        {
            "text": "and it's like we can barely keep up.",
            "start": 91.501,
            "duration": 2.239
        },
        {
            "text": "A lot of the major events\nin this film are shot",
            "start": 94.4,
            "duration": 1.789
        },
        {
            "text": "telephoto, in profile.",
            "start": 96.19,
            "duration": 1.447
        },
        {
            "text": "Actually if you watch the movie again,",
            "start": 97.672,
            "duration": 1.685
        },
        {
            "text": "you'll see that Bong very subtly",
            "start": 99.358,
            "duration": 1.604
        },
        {
            "text": "gives away the important plot points",
            "start": 100.963,
            "duration": 1.552
        },
        {
            "text": "versus the red herrings.",
            "start": 102.516,
            "duration": 1.746
        },
        {
            "text": "So when Mother meets the junkman,",
            "start": 105.6,
            "duration": 1.598
        },
        {
            "text": "who will turn out to be very important,",
            "start": 107.199,
            "duration": 1.976
        },
        {
            "text": "watch the lens.",
            "start": 109.176,
            "duration": 1.0
        },
        {
            "text": "Before that, when Mother\ngoes to apologize",
            "start": 111.457,
            "duration": 1.49
        },
        {
            "text": "to the dead girl's family,",
            "start": 112.948,
            "duration": 1.1
        },
        {
            "text": "watch how this\nimportant moment plays.",
            "start": 114.049,
            "duration": 1.98
        },
        {
            "text": "There's actually a nice\nhidden cut in there.",
            "start": 121.7,
            "duration": 1.643
        },
        {
            "text": "Check that out.",
            "start": 123.344,
            "duration": 1.0
        },
        {
            "text": "If you're wondering whether\nthis is a particular quirk of Bong's,",
            "start": 125.688,
            "duration": 2.165
        },
        {
            "text": "the answer is: kinda.",
            "start": 127.854,
            "duration": 2.047
        },
        {
            "text": "This is the big Act I turning point",
            "start": 129.902,
            "duration": 1.854
        },
        {
            "text": "in his monster movie \"The Host\".",
            "start": 131.757,
            "duration": 1.8
        },
        {
            "text": "Again: telephoto, profile.",
            "start": 133.608,
            "duration": 1.92
        },
        {
            "text": "But here, you can\nkinda understand why.",
            "start": 136.033,
            "duration": 1.899
        },
        {
            "text": "This is a point of view shot\nof another character,",
            "start": 137.933,
            "duration": 2.035
        },
        {
            "text": "and there's actually a nice visual rhyme.",
            "start": 139.969,
            "duration": 1.714
        },
        {
            "text": "Head on.",
            "start": 142.041,
            "duration": 0.7
        },
        {
            "text": "Head on.",
            "start": 143.425,
            "duration": 0.7
        },
        {
            "text": "Profile.",
            "start": 144.95,
            "duration": 0.7
        },
        {
            "text": "And I don't wanna suggest that\nit's unusual to shoot things like this.",
            "start": 146.438,
            "duration": 2.76
        },
        {
            "text": "For example\u2026",
            "start": 149.199,
            "duration": 0.9
        },
        {
            "text": "Man, that's awesome.",
            "start": 155.373,
            "duration": 1.244
        },
        {
            "text": "But it's still really weird\nto use it in \"Mother\".",
            "start": 156.618,
            "duration": 2.446
        },
        {
            "text": "I mean, who's watching?",
            "start": 159.065,
            "duration": 1.439
        },
        {
            "text": "Why's the director\nplaying so many big moments",
            "start": 160.505,
            "duration": 2.419
        },
        {
            "text": "of his lead actress at right angles\nto the camera, in close-up?",
            "start": 162.925,
            "duration": 3.568
        },
        {
            "text": "Then you get to the climax.",
            "start": 168.288,
            "duration": 1.034
        },
        {
            "text": "Big spoilers ahead.",
            "start": 170.256,
            "duration": 1.207
        },
        {
            "text": "We find out that the son,",
            "start": 171.464,
            "duration": 1.506
        },
        {
            "text": "Do-joon, who we've spent the whole movie\nbelieving is probably innocent?",
            "start": 173.723,
            "duration": 3.417
        },
        {
            "text": "Well, he actually\ndid commit the murder.",
            "start": 177.141,
            "duration": 1.926
        },
        {
            "text": "The only witness is the junkman.",
            "start": 182.506,
            "duration": 1.749
        },
        {
            "text": "His mother kills the guy.",
            "start": 184.256,
            "duration": 2.095
        },
        {
            "text": "And then she tries\nto clean up the blood.",
            "start": 187.715,
            "duration": 1.506
        },
        {
            "text": "Oh hey, look at this shot.",
            "start": 190.505,
            "duration": 1.075
        },
        {
            "text": "So that's why he shot those\nbig moments telephoto, in profile.",
            "start": 192.417,
            "duration": 2.894
        },
        {
            "text": "It puts us slightly further away\nfrom the characters.",
            "start": 195.312,
            "duration": 2.552
        },
        {
            "text": "It reminds us that we don't know\neverything in the story;",
            "start": 197.865,
            "duration": 2.665
        },
        {
            "text": "that a lot is hidden from us,",
            "start": 200.531,
            "duration": 1.289
        },
        {
            "text": "or it's far away and it's hazy to see.",
            "start": 201.821,
            "duration": 2.546
        },
        {
            "text": "It turns us into witnesses\nwho can't do anything about it.",
            "start": 204.368,
            "duration": 2.562
        },
        {
            "text": "But once we do see it,",
            "start": 207.747,
            "duration": 0.887
        },
        {
            "text": "we know what we saw.",
            "start": 210.406,
            "duration": 1.337
        },
        {
            "text": "In fact, that's kinda\nthe great thing about this film.",
            "start": 212.59,
            "duration": 1.956
        },
        {
            "text": "You start the movie watching\na character you've never seen before",
            "start": 214.547,
            "duration": 3.173
        },
        {
            "text": "dancing in a field.",
            "start": 217.721,
            "duration": 1.131
        },
        {
            "text": "You can see her face,",
            "start": 218.853,
            "duration": 1.118
        },
        {
            "text": "but you don't understand\nwhy she feels this way.",
            "start": 219.972,
            "duration": 2.535
        },
        {
            "text": "You just trust that\nthe movie will explain it.",
            "start": 222.508,
            "duration": 2.189
        },
        {
            "text": "Then at the end,\nyou see her dancing again.",
            "start": 224.898,
            "duration": 2.168
        },
        {
            "text": "Telephoto, in profile.",
            "start": 227.067,
            "duration": 1.9
        },
        {
            "text": "And you don't really understand her\nany better than you did at the beginning.",
            "start": 228.968,
            "duration": 4.353
        },
        {
            "text": "For two hours,\nthe biggest bedrock of this movie",
            "start": 233.322,
            "duration": 2.538
        },
        {
            "text": "is that we know, for a fact,\nthat she loves her son.",
            "start": 235.861,
            "duration": 2.645
        },
        {
            "text": "And at the end, we see all this\nhas brought on her.",
            "start": 239.158,
            "duration": 3.69
        },
        {
            "text": "If you can't tell, I'm a big fan\nof this movie and of Bong Joon-ho.",
            "start": 244.146,
            "duration": 3.156
        },
        {
            "text": "I also really wish more\nmainstream directors",
            "start": 247.303,
            "duration": 2.317
        },
        {
            "text": "would be ballsy enough\nto shoot their big plot moments",
            "start": 249.621,
            "duration": 2.882
        },
        {
            "text": "like this.",
            "start": 252.504,
            "duration": 0.807
        },
        {
            "text": "Instead of like this.",
            "start": 256.022,
            "duration": 1.117
        },
        {
            "text": "Agh. God!\nI gotta get a drink.",
            "start": 259.255,
            "duration": 2.937
        },
        {
            "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community",
            "start": 266.0,
            "duration": 3.0
        }
    ]
}